    <h1 class="heading1">Neurology Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our Neurology Department is committed to providing comprehensive care for patients with neurological disorders affecting the brain, spinal cord, nerves, and muscles. Led by board-certified neurologists and supported by a team of skilled healthcare professionals, we offer a wide range of services to diagnose, treat, and manage neurological conditions.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Neurological Consultation</h4>
            <p>Our neurologists provide thorough consultations to evaluate and diagnose a variety of neurological conditions, including headaches, seizures, strokes, movement disorders, neuropathies, and neurodegenerative diseases such as Alzheimer's disease and Parkinson's disease. We utilize advanced diagnostic techniques and imaging studies to accurately diagnose neurological conditions and develop personalized treatment plans.</p>

            <h4>Electrodiagnostic Testing</h4>
            <p>We offer a range of electrodiagnostic tests, including electromyography (EMG) and nerve conduction studies (NCS), to evaluate and diagnose disorders of the nerves and muscles. These tests help our neurologists assess nerve and muscle function, identify abnormalities, and guide treatment decisions for conditions such as peripheral neuropathy, carpal tunnel syndrome, and myasthenia gravis.</p>

            <h4>Stroke Care</h4>
            <p>Our Neurology Department specializes in stroke care, providing rapid evaluation, diagnosis, and treatment for patients experiencing stroke symptoms. We offer advanced stroke treatments, including intravenous thrombolysis (IV tPA) and mechanical thrombectomy, to restore blood flow to the brain and minimize disability after a stroke. Our stroke team works collaboratively to provide timely and comprehensive care for stroke patients.</p>

            <h4>Epilepsy Management</h4>
            <p>We provide comprehensive care for patients with epilepsy and seizure disorders, including diagnostic testing, medication management, and surgical evaluation for refractory epilepsy. Our neurologists work closely with patients to develop individualized treatment plans aimed at controlling seizures, improving quality of life, and minimizing side effects of treatment.</p>

            <h4>Memory Disorders Clinic</h4>
            <p>Our Memory Disorders Clinic offers specialized care for patients with memory loss and cognitive impairment, including Alzheimer's disease, mild cognitive impairment (MCI), and other forms of dementia. Our neurologists conduct thorough evaluations, including cognitive assessments and imaging studies, to diagnose memory disorders and develop personalized care plans to manage symptoms and support patients and their families.</p>

            <h4>Movement Disorders Clinic</h4>
            <p>For patients with movement disorders such as Parkinson's disease, essential tremor, and dystonia, our Movement Disorders Clinic provides expert evaluation and management. Our neurologists offer advanced treatments, including medication adjustments, deep brain stimulation (DBS) therapy, and botulinum toxin injections, to improve motor symptoms and enhance quality of life for patients with movement disorders.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
        <div class="cl">
            <h3>State-of-the-Art Facilities</h3>
            <p>Aatura Hospital is equipped with advanced technology and state-of-the-art facilities to support our Neurology Department's efforts. From our neuroimaging center and electrodiagnostic lab to our stroke unit and epilepsy monitoring unit, we have the resources needed to provide comprehensive diagnostic and treatment services for neurological conditions.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content3">
        <div class="cl">
            <h3>Patient-Centered Care</h3>
            <p>At Aatura Hospital, we prioritize patient-centered care, focusing on the individual needs and concerns of each patient. Our neurologists take the time to listen to patients' symptoms, answer their questions, and involve them in decision-making regarding their neurological health. We strive to create a supportive and compassionate environment where patients feel heard, valued, and empowered to participate in their care.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="content4">
        <div class="cl">
            <h3>Contact Us</h3>
            <p>If you or a loved one is experiencing neurological symptoms or has been diagnosed with a neurological condition, don't hesitate to reach out to us. Our Neurology Department is here to provide expert care and support to help you manage your condition and improve your quality of life.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

